 Patients Inclusion Criteria - Informed consent - Thoracolumbar pedicle screw placement - Indication for surgery: Degenerative pathologies (stenosis, spondylolisthesis, degenerative disc disease, recurrent disc herniation), infections, tumors, fractures, trauma - Age 18 Exclusion Criteria - Deformity surgery (>5 index levels) Patients will be thoroughly informed about the techniques, risks and backgrounds of the pertaining procedure.

 This is a prospective study.

 Analysis will occur on a per protocol basis.

 To provide optimal treatment quality, the procedures will be carried out surgeon-based: This means that surgeons who are most experienced in using robotic guidance will carry out all RG procedures and surgeons most experienced in using the free hand technique will carry out all FH procedures, etc.

 Data Management Each participating center will maintain a proprietary database, with identical structure.

 The databases should be kept anonymous, with each center maintaining its own, separate key that links study-specific patient numbers to birthdate and name.

 Twice yearly (1.

